One of the easiest desserts to make. I love the simplicity of this recipe, all the ingredients are always in my house. I use frozen mixed berries in the winter time and reduce the sugar for both the filling and topping because I like to taste more fruit than sugar. The only addition I make to this recipe is the juice of one lemon to the fruit mixture. Serve with either vanilla ice cream or a mascarpone/whipped cream mixture. I love this recipe.

