Rating: 4
This recipe is so fantastic, I make it all the time in the summer. I also like to modify it a little each time, playing with flavors and spices (I usually add nutmeg and clove to the topping, as well as cinnamon). My parents have a lavender farm, so I often experiment with culinary lavender. Try crumbling up 1-2 tablespoons culinary lavender bud and mixing it in with the berries. Subtle, but delicious - people won't be able to put their finger on it, but they'll know it tastes more "gourmet" than the average berry crisp.

